  "body": "<!--\r\n\r\n    Please do *NOT* ask usage questions in Github issues.\r\n\r\n    If your issue is not a feature request or bug report use:\r\n    https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/prometheus-users. If\r\n    you are unsure whether you hit a bug, search and ask in the\r\n    mailing list first.\r\n\r\n    You can find more information at: https://prometheus.io/community/\r\n\r\n-->\r\n## Proposal\r\n\r\nThe current Kubernetes service discovery implementation totally disregard initContainers.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/blob/master/discovery/kubernetes/pod.go#L216\r\n\r\nThis would be useful to have them scrape because:\r\n- they may contain troubleshooting information.\r\n- We could detect problems.\r\n- We might want to observe how long initialization took.\r\n\r\nOriginally the problem appeared from https://github.com/grafana/loki/issues/575  while for metrics it is arguable that you might need this, for logs there is no question.\r\n\r\nAlternatives could be to create a custom service discovery. /cc @gouthamve ",
